overview: The user initiated a request for a comprehensive review of a recently
  developed smart patient interactive sleep questionnaire application. The
  primary goal was to ensure that the implemented database, API endpoints, and
  overall functionality adhered to the acceptance criteria detailed in the
  provided Statement of Work. The application is intended to be a freemium
  service, collecting minimal de-identified demographic data (year of birth,
  zipcode/county, sex). It should generate narrative reports with tailored
  guidance, educational links, and references to clinicians, either pointing
  towards sleep health optimization or providing probable diagnoses for a
  defined set of sleep disorders. The assistant began the review process by
  systematically examining key project files, including the questionnaire's
  structure, data types, validation logic, Prisma schema, API routes for
  handling responses, CSV export, PDF report generation, and relevant UI
  components like the  and admin dashboard.
